<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 05 at 7:03PM EST  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>... PATCHY DENSE FOG POSSIBLE THROUGH MIDNIGHT ...
Patchy dense fog is possible the first half of this evening across
the Connecticut River Valley. Visibilities may be reduced to one
quarter mile at times. Improvements in visibility are expected
after midnight.
Motorists are advised to exercise caution by reducing speed,
leaving extra space between vehicles, and using low-beam
headlights in areas of low visibility.</description>
